<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi fontstyle="italic">jωn</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{e rSup { size 8{jωn} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> the eigen-function. Actually, the phase of the input signal 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mi>e</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mi fontstyle="italic">jωn</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{e rSup { size 8{jωn} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> has been change. For this we write</para>
